        <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-extrabold text-gray-900 leading-tight mb-6">SEO Best Practices for 2024</h1>

        <div class="prose prose-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed max-w-none prose-red">
            <p class="mb-4">Search Engine Optimization (SEO) is constantly evolving, with search engines like Google regularly updating their algorithms. To ensure your website ranks well and attracts organic traffic, it's crucial to implement the latest SEO best practices. Here are key strategies for 2024:</p>

            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">1. Focus on User Experience (UX)</h3>
            <p class="mb-4">Google prioritizes websites that offer an excellent user experience. This includes fast loading times, mobile-friendliness, intuitive navigation, and engaging content. Core Web Vitals, a set of metrics related to speed, responsiveness, and visual stability, are now significant ranking factors.</p>

            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">2. High-Quality, Relevant Content</h3>
            <p class="mb-4">Content remains king. Create comprehensive, well-researched, and valuable content that directly addresses your audience's needs and questions. Focus on long-form content, evergreen topics, and diverse formats like videos, infographics, and podcasts to increase engagement.</p>

            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">3. Semantic SEO and Entity Optimization</h3>
            <p class="mb-4">Beyond keywords, search engines now understand the context and relationships between entities. Optimize your content for semantic search by using related terms, synonyms, and structured data (Schema markup) to help search engines understand the meaning and context of your content.</p>

            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">4. Mobile-First Indexing</h3>
            <p class="mb-4">Mobile-first indexing means Google primarily uses the mobile version of your website for ranking. Ensure your site is fully responsive and optimized for mobile devices, providing a seamless experience for users on smartphones and tablets.</p>

            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">5. E-A-T Principles (Expertise, Authoritativeness, Trustworthiness)</h3>
            <p class="mb-4">E-A-T is crucial, especially for YMYL (Your Money Your Life) topics. Demonstrate your expertise, establish authoritativeness through credible sources and backlinks, and build trustworthiness with transparent information and secure website practices. Author bios, certifications, and strong external links contribute to E-A-T.</p>

            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">6. Voice Search Optimization</h3>
            <p class="mb-4">With the rise of voice assistants, optimizing for voice search is becoming increasingly important. Focus on natural language, long-tail keywords, and conversational phrases. Voice search queries are typically longer and more question-based.</p>

            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">7. Local SEO</h3>
            <p class="mb-4">For businesses with a physical presence, local SEO is vital. Optimize your Google My Business profile, ensure consistent NAP (Name, Address, Phone Number) information across all online directories, and encourage local reviews to attract nearby customers.</p>

            <p class="mt-6">By integrating these SEO best practices, you can enhance your website's visibility, attract more qualified leads, and achieve sustainable growth in 2024 and beyond.</p>
